{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1783589714,"nonce":"LJ89fpV05R02wPvRHHPPZgYDFkA=","message":"Phase 2 PR **2.0d MERGED** (squash `948b403`, PR #95) — runtime↔model CTE render unification.\n\nRemoved the second CTE rendering implementation: `CteDef::body()` now yields a neutral `ViewBody`\n(recursive body = `ViewBody::Set{Union}`); both runtime `write_cte_prefix`s (core + test backend)\nroute through the shared `render_with_prefix` from 2.0c; deleted `CteBody`, `render_cte_body`,\n`render_recursive_cte_body`. The `CteDef` trait stays (runtime `'static` type-driven collection).\n\nRecursive-arm rendering is now **dialect-aware** (new `Dialect::supports_parenthesized_recursive_cte_arm`\nseam, default true / SQLite false): a plain tail-less arm renders bare (fixing a latent SQLite bug — SQLite\nrejects a parenthesized recursive arm, which the old runtime path always emitted), a scoped arm (own\nORDER BY/LIMIT/OFFSET) renders parenthesized on PG/MySQL and is rejected on SQLite. This also lets\nrecursive-CTE **view** bodies with a scoped anchor render on PG/MySQL, which 2.0c could not. Recursion\ndetection is gated on the clause-level `WITH RECURSIVE` flag so a plain `WITH` whose CTE shadows a\nrelation name is not misclassified as recursive.\n\nReview: local `codex review` loop, 4 rounds (dialect-aware seam; deferred-plumbing git-bug; clause-flag\ngate; clean). **NEW PROCESS (2026-07-09): the GitHub `@codex` bot review cycle is dropped — review is\nlocal via `codex review`; a PR is still the merge vehicle (branch-protection ruleset requires PR + `test`\nCI).**\n\n**Split off → new git-bug `1e67ff8`:** the runtime query render (`to_sql`) is infallible, so a SQLite\nquery using a recursive CTE with a scoped arm surfaces the SQLite reject as a panic rather than a returned\nerror (the shape was already non-functional on SQLite). Fix = plumb a fallible runtime render. Documented\non `RecursiveCteDefinition` as an interim limitation.\n\n**Next (per plan):** per-backend view-body introspection — 2.1 PostgreSQL → 2.2 MySQL → 2.3 SQLite (each\nneeds a `canonical_view_*` normalization; see the phase2 plan carry-forward).","files":null}]}